{"word":"ἀναμιμνήσκω","slug":"ἀναμιμνήσκω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀναμιμνήσκω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to remind</i> one <i>of</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> dupl. <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>ταῦτά μ' ἀνέμνησας</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <el>ἀν. τινά τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to remind</i> one to do, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to recall to memory, make mention of</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to remember</i>, <el>τινός</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; more rarely <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>περί τι</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}